Vice President Biden met with Vice President Sambo of Nigeria at the White House to discuss peace and prosperity in Nigeria and the West African region. Biden offered condolences for the lives lost in Boko Haram attacks and expressed strong support for Nigeria's efforts to improve socioeconomic and security conditions. They also discussed cooperation on trade, investment, peace and security in West Africa, and counterterrorism. Biden thanked Sambo for Nigeria's leadership in addressing unrest in other African countries. Sambo reaffirmed his government's commitment to expanding services, access to electricity, infrastructure development, and improving the quality of life for Nigerian citizens.